{% comment %}
  * A cropped image that fills the container width using background-size: cover
  * height is defined by the optional aspect ratio.  If aspect ratio is false or nil
  * the image will use natural height and will not be cropped.

  *  img_object {object}- The Image we will use
  *  aspect_ratio {float} - The aspect ratio of the image in the format {ratio}:1

  {% render 'image-fill', img_object: section.settings.image, aspect_ratio: section.settings.aspect_ratio %}
{% endcomment %}

{%- assign default_image = 'blank.svg' | asset_url -%}
{%- assign image = img_object | default: default_image -%}
{%- assign bg_position = bg_position | default: "center-center" -%}
{%- comment -%}
  `sizes` parameter (added 2026-04-26): tells the browser the rendered
  width of the image so it can pick the right srcset variant. Default
  remains "100vw" for backward compat with full-width hero/banner uses.
  Card-context callers (article-grid-item, list-collections, etc.)
  should pass an accurate sizes hint like
  "(min-width: 768px) 25vw, 50vw" — the OVERSIZED-WASTE finding from
  the 2026-04-25 smoke test showed cards rendered at 294px wide were
  loading 720x/1080x variants because of the 100vw hint.
{%- endcomment -%}
{%- assign sizes = sizes | default: "100vw" -%}
{%- comment -%}
  loading + fetchpriority params (added 2026-04-28).
  Default loading="lazy" preserves prior behavior for the 90%+ of
  callers rendering below-the-fold images. Above-the-fold callers
  (first gallery block, hero section, etc.) should explicitly pass
  loading: 'eager' AND fetchpriority: 'high' to avoid being penalised
  by Lighthouse's lcp-discovery-insight (which scored 0 on
  /pages/azta-urban-salon-service-menu in the 2026-04-28 audit
  because the gallery's first image was lazy-loaded — but it was the
  LCP element, so lazy-load directly delays LCP). 782 KiB of image
  delivery savings + faster LCP unblock from this single change.

  Pattern for section callers iterating blocks:
    {%- if forloop.first -%}
      {%- render 'image-fill', img_object: ..., loading: 'eager', fetchpriority: 'high' -%}
    {%- else -%}
      {%- render 'image-fill', img_object: ... -%}
    {%- endif -%}
{%- endcomment -%}
{%- assign loading = loading | default: 'lazy' -%}
{%- assign fetchpriority = fetchpriority | default: '' -%}

{%- comment -%}
  Native <img loading="lazy"> instead of the legacy
  <div class="lazyload" data-bgset> CSS-background pattern. Browser
  handles intersection natively (faster than lazysizes JS), no
  data-bgset srcset list to evaluate (4 width steps via srcset
  instead of 18). The aspect-ratio reservation on the parent
  .image__fill (padding-top) is preserved so there's no CLS;
  the inner img is positioned absolute to fill it with object-fit:
  cover, mirroring the prior background-size: cover behavior.

  bg_position param (e.g., "center-center") still honored via
  object-position so existing per-instance crops are preserved.
{%- endcomment -%}
<div class="image__fill fade-in-child"
  {% if image contains 'blank.svg' %}
    style="padding-top: {{ aspect_ratio | times: 100 }}%;
           filter: brightness(.95);"
  {% elsif aspect_ratio %}
    style="padding-top: {{ aspect_ratio | times: 100}}%;
           background-image: url('{{ image | image_url: width: 1, height: 1 }}');"
  {% else %}
    style="padding-top: {{ 1 | divided_by: image.aspect_ratio | times: 100}}%;
           background-image: url('{{ image | image_url: width: 1, height: 1 }}');"
  {% endif %}>
  {%- if image contains 'blank.svg' -%}
  {%- else -%}
    {%- comment -%}
      Hot fix 2026-04-26: removed `background-size-cover` from the img
      class. The CSS rule `.fade-in-child .background-size-cover` sets
      opacity:0 by default and only flips to opacity:1 when lazysizes
      adds the `.lazyloaded` class. Native <img loading="lazy"> never
      gets that class, so the image stays invisible forever even after
      it loads. The class was a leftover from the old CSS-background
      pattern and isn't needed here — `object-fit:cover` is already
      applied via inline style. Issue first surfaced on homepage blog
      cards + article-page recommended-articles sidebar.
    {%- endcomment -%}
    {%- comment -%}
      WebP rollout 2026-04-28 — same <picture>+<source> pattern shipped
      for product-grid-item.liquid (commit e946c02). image_url filter
      with format:'webp' returns Shopify-CDN-served WebP variants —
      typically 30-50% smaller than JPG at equivalent quality.

      Modern browsers (~98% of HairMNL traffic per CrUX) pick the WebP
      via type negotiation on <source>. Older browsers fall through to
      the <img> JPG/PNG below. Lighthouse modern-image-formats audit
      moves from FAIL to PASS for these images.

      Critical pattern detail: pass `image` (the raw Image object)
      into image_url, NOT image.src (URL string) — the latter silently
      drops the format param. Earlier WebP attempts on banner-slider
      and product-grid-item failed twice because of this.

      The <img> below stays as fallback (and so existing JS / DevTools
      tooling that reads img.src still works). width/height + loading
      + fetchpriority + style + alt all remain on <img> per HTML spec
      — those don't go on <source>.
    {%- endcomment -%}
    <picture>
      <source type="image/webp"
              srcset="{% if image.width > 360 %}{{ image | image_url: width: 360, format: 'webp' }} 360w,{% endif %}
                      {% if image.width > 720 %}{{ image | image_url: width: 720, format: 'webp' }} 720w,{% endif %}
                      {% if image.width > 1080 %}{{ image | image_url: width: 1080, format: 'webp' }} 1080w,{% endif %}
                      {% if image.width > 1600 %}{{ image | image_url: width: 1600, format: 'webp' }} 1600w,{% endif %}"
              sizes="{{ sizes }}">
      <img
        class="fade-in-child"
        srcset="{% if image.width > 360 %}{{ image | image_url: width: 360 }} 360w,{% endif %}
                {% if image.width > 720 %}{{ image | image_url: width: 720 }} 720w,{% endif %}
                {% if image.width > 1080 %}{{ image | image_url: width: 1080 }} 1080w,{% endif %}
                {% if image.width > 1600 %}{{ image | image_url: width: 1600 }} 1600w,{% endif %}
                {{ image | image_url: 'master' }} {{ image.width }}w"
        sizes="{{ sizes }}"
        src="{{ image | image_url: 'master' }}"
        width="{{ image.width }}"
        height="{{ image.height }}"
        loading="{{ loading }}"
        {% if fetchpriority != '' %}fetchpriority="{{ fetchpriority }}"{% endif %}
        alt="{{ image.alt | strip_html | escape }}"
        style="position:absolute;top:0;left:0;width:100%;height:100%;object-fit:cover;object-position:{{ bg_position | replace: '-', ' ' }};">
    </picture>
  {%- endif -%}
  <noscript>
    <img src="{{ image | image_url: width: 720 }}" alt="{{ image.alt | strip_html | escape }}" class="responsive-wide-image"/>
  </noscript>
</div>
